      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match VAD operating envelope (flow rate, rotational speed, hematocrit) within stated tolerances at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data were collected at three of five required operating points. Hematocrit was fixed at 33% rather than the physiological range of 30–45%. Test condition coverage insufficient for Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., NRMSE) between predicted and measured hemolysis index must be below 15% across all validation operating points at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "NRMSE of 28% observed across available validation points. Systematic over-prediction at high rotational speed. Achieved Gradation 2; gap to Gradation 4 is substantial."
